# REST API Design Patterns
## 🚨 CONTRACT-FIRST (MANDATORY)

### DO

* Always implement APIs based on OpenAPI contract
* Contract location: `design-inputs/api-contracts/task-tracker.yaml`
* Validate request/response against contract before coding

### DO NOT

* Do not implement endpoints without contract
* Do not deviate from contract

---

## 🌐 URL STRUCTURE

### DO

* Use plural nouns:

  * `/tasks`
* Use lowercase
* Use hierarchical structure:

  * `/tasks/{id}`

### STANDARD PATTERNS

```
GET    /tasks              # Get all tasks
GET    /tasks/{id}         # Get task by id
POST   /tasks              # Create task
PUT    /tasks/{id}         # Update task
PATCH  /tasks/{id}         # Partial update
DELETE /tasks/{id}         # Delete task
```

---

## 🔍 QUERY PARAMETERS

### DO

* Filtering: `?status=COMPLETED`
* Pagination: `?page=1&limit=10`
* Sorting: `?sort=createdAt` or `?sort=-createdAt`

### DO NOT

* Do not overload endpoints with complex query logic

---

## 🔁 HTTP METHODS

### DO

* GET → read
* POST → create
* PUT → full update
* PATCH → partial update
* DELETE → remove

### DO NOT

* Do not misuse HTTP methods
* Do not use POST for updates

---

## 📊 STATUS CODES

### SUCCESS

* 200 OK → GET, PUT, PATCH
* 201 CREATED → POST
* 204 NO CONTENT → DELETE

### CLIENT ERRORS

* 400 BAD REQUEST → validation errors
* 404 NOT FOUND → resource missing

### SERVER ERROR

* 500 INTERNAL SERVER ERROR

---

## 📦 RESPONSE FORMAT

### SUCCESS RESPONSE

```
{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Task title",
  "description": "Task desc",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "createdAt": "2026-01-01T10:00:00Z"
}
```

---

### LIST RESPONSE

```
{
  "data": [],
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 20
  }
}
```

---

### ERROR RESPONSE

```
{
  "statusCode": 400,
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "errors": [
    {
      "field": "title",
      "message": "must not be blank"
    }
  ],
  "timestamp": "2026-01-01T10:00:00Z",
  "path": "/tasks"
}
```

---

## 🔄 VERSIONING

### DO

* Use URL versioning:

```
/v1/tasks
```

### DO NOT

* Do not introduce breaking changes without versioning

---

## 🔁 IDEMPOTENCY

### DO

* Ensure:

  * GET, PUT, PATCH, DELETE → idempotent

---

## 🧾 HEADERS

### REQUEST

```
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
```

### RESPONSE

```
Content-Type: application/json
Location: /tasks/{id}
```

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep APIs simple
* Validate all inputs
* Return created resource on POST
* Use DTOs only

### DO NOT

* Do not expose entities
* Do not return stack traces
* Do not create deeply nested responses

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST follow endpoint patterns
* MUST use correct HTTP status codes
* MUST validate inputs
* MUST use DTOs
* MUST follow OpenAPI contract
* MUST NOT generate endpoints without spec

